on the demand side, spot has paid + unpaid users, thus its addressable market & the data that comes with it will out scale nflx. on the supply side, spot has all music content available, and not just numtkn-numtkn% of the video people watch on a daily basis as nflx does.

spotify widely considered to have a great recommendation engine, quickly getting the listener to music they like. compared to nflx, spot has a wider relative funnel on both the demand & supply side, and also has no incentive of what content to favor when making a recommendation.

biggest challenge for nflx to solve = curation, which opens a path for a 3rd party using reviews/social media to wedge itself between the viewer, the decision of what to watch, & the content. nflx's incentive to keep its data private + favor its owned content are related factors. linktkn
